Allocate Elastic IP address 
----------------------------
Elastic IP address setting
\_Amazon's Pool of IPv4 addresses   -> This is default and most common option  = Means : AWS gives you a public IPv4 from its own pool 
\_BYOIP ->Bring Your Own IP         -> This means you bring your own public IPv4 addresses that you own outside AWS 
\_Customer-owned Pool               -> Used when you run AWS  outposts in your data centers 
\_Allocate  using IPv4 IPAM pood    -> This option allocate Elastic IP  from an IP pool you have configured in VPC IPAM 


Network Border Group :
This defines where AWS can allocate an Elastic IP from 

Global static IP addresses: 
This is not part of Elastic IP ,This is AWS promoting  AWS Global ACcelerator ,which gives 

Global Static IP (works worldwide)
Anycast routing â†’ Fastest path via AWS Edge network
High availability
Cross-region failover

Elastic IPs are regional ,but global accelerator IPs are global 
They give globallly accessible Ip's 

